This paper deals with online learning of Markov decision processes (MDPs) with function approximation, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of bandit algorithms, which are commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence, but also has applications in control systems and robotics (cs.MA).
